description:
Once upon a time, I had a slightly different, or rather, quite different meaning of what you have to do in life, it was a very objective meaning with achievable goals and realistic objectives about what I wanted my life to be, but over time I started to change all that x something quite different, something more subjective and that fitted my way of thinking and I started to form my life purpose....
In fact for most people, more than a goal, it is a way of seeing life, but for me it became my goal, something I longed for and I never knew if it was what I really thought or if I was just fooling myself, and I am talking about my goal in life was simply to live, there is a phrase that I love that says that if you are going to be afraid of living it is better not to be born, and I agree at all, really a life of calm is not a life, the meaning of life for me is chaos, all the beautiful and perfect chaos that makes up every single thing you do in the world, every anecdote, every meal, every story and every memory, everything is generated by chaos and by not being afraid of living and enjoying chaos....
